---
description: Rules for the browser MIDI-from-text app
globs: src/**/*.ts,src/**/*.tsx
alwaysApply: false
---

- Treat music parsing, prompt interpretation, score generation, and MIDI export as separate concerns.
- Keep business logic in pure utility functions.
- Keep React hooks orchestration-focused, not logic-heavy.
- Never generate MIDI directly from raw prompt text.
- Always convert user input into a canonical typed score model first.
- Prefer deterministic algorithms over randomness.
- Favor motif + variation for melody generation.
- Keep prompt interpretation explainable through assumptions and confidence.
- When changing export logic, ensure previewed notes and exported MIDI stay identical.
- Briefly explain planned file changes before editing.
- Report build/lint status after changes.